  "prompt": "How has technology changed education?",
  "response": "Technology has transformed education in several key ways:\n\n1. Access to Information\n- Online resources and digital libraries\n- Easy access to educational content worldwide\n- Free online courses and learning platforms\n\n2. Learning Tools\n- Interactive educational software\n- Educational apps and games\n- Digital textbooks and multimedia content\n\n3. Communication\n- Video conferencing for remote learning\n- Collaboration tools\n- Easy communication between students and teachers\n\n4. Personalized Learning\n- Adaptive learning technologies\n- Customized learning paths\n- Individual pace of learning\n\n5. Classroom Technology\n- Smart boards and digital displays\n- Tablets and laptops in classrooms\n- Online assignment submissions\n\n6. Global Connectivity\n- International learning opportunities\n- Cultural exchange through technology\n- Virtual field trips and global classrooms\n\n7. Skills Development\n- Teaching digital literacy\n- Preparing students for technology-driven workplaces\n- Learning coding and technical skills\n\n8. Assessment\n- Online testing\n- Instant feedback\n- Data-driven performance tracking\n\n9. Accessibility\n- Learning options for students with disabilities\n- Remote and flexible learning\n- Breaking geographical barriers\n\nThese changes have made education more interactive, accessible, and adaptable to individual learning needs.",
